        "detail": "While joint ownership can work for partnerships, this provision allows either party to license joint IP to anyone (including competitors) without consent from the other party and without revenue sharing ('without accounting'). This could undermine the partnership value if one party licenses to our competitors or commercializes more aggressively without sharing benefits.",
        "recommendation": "NEGOTIATE: Add restrictions on licensing to direct competitors, OR require mutual consent for third-party licenses, OR add revenue sharing for joint IP exploitation ('with accounting to the other party')."
      }
    ]
  }
}

